{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_91","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' code/sycophancy-interpretability/evaluation/README.md\"","aggregated_output":"<!--\n * @Author             : 陈蔚 (cy424151@alibaba-inc.com)\n * @Date               : 2024-10-16 21:26\n * @Last Modified By   : 殊理 (husile.hsl@alibaba-inc.com)\n * @Last Modified Date : 2024-10-18 15:38\n * @Description        : \n * -------- \n * Copyright (c) 2024 Alibaba Inc. \n-->\n\n# Evaluation Scripts for Sycophancy and Universal Ability\n\nWe provide a full list of scripts used to evaluate the performance of the models on the Sycophancy and Universal Ability, which is contained in our paper.\n\n## 1. Data\n\nFor ease of use, we directly provide the processed data in the `datasets` folder.\n\nAlternatively, you can download the raw data and process the data yourself following `prepare_evaluation_data.ipynb`.\n\n## 2. Evaluation\n\nWe write the evaluation code in vLLM instead of relying on existing evaluation library for flexibility.\n\n- For generation evaluation datasets, we provide python scripts named `evaluate_${dataset}_chat_vllm.py`;\n- For multiple choice dataset without CoT, we provide python scripts named `evaluate_${dataset}.py`\n\n### 2.1 Sycophancy Evaluation\n\nWe test sycophancy in multi-round conversations setting:\n\n1. The LLM answers the question.\n2. The user challenges the LLM.\n3. The LLM answers the question again.\n\nA ideal LLM should be able to keep the correct answer while modifying the false answer since previous works have shown that the truthfulness inside LLMs is much higher than it actually behaves.\n\nYou can run the following command to generate the conversation between the LLM and the user.\n\n```bash\npython evaluate_sycophancy_chat_vllm.py --model_path $model_path --data_path datasets/sycophancy_eval/free_generation.jsonl\npython evaluate_sycophancy_chat_vllm.py --model_path $model_path --data_path datasets/sycophancy_eval/multiple_choice.jsonl\npython evaluate_sycophancy_chat_vllm.py --model_path $model_path --data_path datasets/sycophancy_eval/multiple_choice_cot.jsonl\n```\n\nWe use open-source LLMs to evaluate the correctness of the answer generated by the LLM in each round.\n\n```bash\npython score_answer_correctness.py --model_path $model_path --eval_model_path $eval_model_path --results_dir results/sycophancy_eval/free_generation\n```\n\nAlso, we use open-source LLMs to evaluate the evluate the sycophancy behavior of the LLM in each round.\n\n```bash\npython score_answer_apologies.py --model_path $model_path --eval_model_path $eval_model_path --results_dir results/sycophancy_eval/free_generation\npython score_answer_apologies.py --model_path $model_path --eval_model_path $eval_model_path --results_dir results/sycophancy_eval/multiple_choice\npython score_answer_apologies.py --model_path $model_path --eval_model_path $eval_model_path --results_dir results/sycophancy_eval/multiple_choice_cot\n```\n\nFinally, we show the sycophancy evaluation results.\n\n```bash\npython print_sycophancy_eval_results.py --model_path $model_path\n```\n\n\n### 2.2 Universal Evaluation\n\nPlease refer to `run_full_evaluation.sh` for the scripts to evaluate the universal ability of the LLM.\n\n## Acknowledgement\n\nWe borrow some code from [Qwen](https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen) evaluation codes.","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
